---
description: "Backend import guardrails"
globs:
  - "backend/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Keep imports at module top level only; no in-function imports.
- Respect hierarchy: `database/` -> `utils/` -> `routers/` -> `main.py`.
- Higher-level modules can import lower-level modules only.
- Keep large-object cleanup patterns in mind (`del`, `.clear()`).
- See AGENTS.md for full rules.
